cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper focuses on improving human segmentation using motion information extracted from videos, which is a common task in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a memory-network-based policy model and uses reinforcement learning, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with video processing, which falls under multimedia (MM) and robotics (RO), making them possible sub-categories as well.
